North Korea’s foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that extending sanctions would deepen distrust in the United States and that it is impossible for his country to unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the annual General Assembly of the global council that in North Korea "significant measures have been implemented to prove their good faith" last year, such as halting nuclear testing and missile testing, dismantling the nuclear testing site and the commitment to nuclear non-proliferation and weapons technology.
"However, we do not see any appropriate response from the United States," he said.
